own","description":"Bilbo’s relative who took silver spoons labeled 'For Lobelia Sackville-Baggins, as a PRESENT'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over spoons and left with them."},{"name":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s heir (before Frodo’s adoption) who demanded to see Frodo’s will.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over the will and left in frustration."},{"name":"Sancho Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Old Odo Proudfoot’s grandson who excavated the pantry seeking Bilbo’s gold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Attempted to excavate the pantry and was ejected by Frodo."},{"name":"Merry Brandybuck","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Frodo’s friend who assisted in managing the chaos at Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Helped manage the crowd and mediated with the Sackville-Bagginses."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Shire","aliases":["Shire of the Hobbits","Bag End","Bagshot Row"],"arc":"The Shire's Transition and Hidden Threats","description":"A fertile region in Eriador where Hobbits live in peace, known for its well-ordered farms and communities.","recentEvents":"Frodo Baggins is managing the aftermath of Bilbo's departure, dealing with visitors and chaos at Bag End.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Adjacent region to the east"},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Historical homeland of Hobbits before settling in the Shire"}]},{"name":"Bree","aliases":["Bree-land"],"description":"A key crossroads town in Eriador, home to the Butterbur family and a hub for travelers."