vents":"Spoke about Bilbo's treasure, discussed the party, and interacted with guests."},{"name":"Sam Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE SHADOW OF THE PAST","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Son of Ham Gamgee, helped maintain Bag End's garden and was curious about Bilbo's stories.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and employee"}],"recentEvents":"Eavesdropped on Frodo and Gandalf's conversation about the Ring"},{"name":"Old Noakes","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Hobbit from Bywater who discussed rumors about Frodo's family.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Commented on Frodo's Brandybuck heritage and Bilbo's wealth."},{"name":"Daddy Twofoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Neighbor of the Gaffer, known for his opinions on local matters.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Neighbor"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke about the Brandybucks and their connection to the Old Forest."},{"name":"Stranger from Michel Delving","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Michel Delving","description":"Visitor from the Westfarthing who speculated about Bilbo's treasure.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Talked about Bilbo's rumored tunnels and wealth."},{"name":"Sackville-Bagginses","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Family of hobbits who scowled at Bilbo's announcement.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed in wrath after Bilbo's disappearance."},