 path, warned of dangers, and advised caution."},{"name":"Gollum [Sméagol]","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE COUNCIL OF ELROND","currentLocation":"Mirkwood (imprisoned)","description":"A corrupted hobbit who possesses the One Ring and is driven by its power.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Enemy"},{"character":"Déagol","relationship":"Murdered friend"},{"character":"Elves","relationship":"Imprisoned"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Former owner of the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Escaped from Mirkwood Elves, revealed his possession of the Ring to Gandalf"},{"name":"Thorin Oakenshield","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Of the Finding of the Ring","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Leader of the dwarves on a quest for treasure, slain in the Battle of Five Armies.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Died in the Battle of Five Armies, with his hoard destroyed."},{"name":"Ham Gamgee","aliases":["the Gaffer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Old gardener and friend of Bilbo and Frodo, known for his tales of Bilbo's wealth.","relationships":[{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke about Bilbo's treasure, discussed the party, and interacted with guests."},{"name":"Sam Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","the Gaffer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3: THE RING GOES SOUTH","currentLocation":"High moor","description":"Frodo's loyal gardener and companion. Noted the Black Rider's presence and provided crucial information about the stranger in Hobbiton.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Companion and protector"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Companion and friend"},{"character":"Fro, Baggins","relationship":"Traveling companion"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Rescued by"},{"character":"Goldberry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Suspicious of"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Companion"}],"recentEvents":"Carried supplies, took watch, and endured the journey's hardships."},{"name":"Old Noakes","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Hobbit from Bywater who discussed rumors about Frodo's family.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Commented on Frodo's Brandybuck heritage and Bilbo's wealth."},{"name":"Daddy Twofoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Neighbor of the Gaffer, known for his opinions on local matters.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Neighbor"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke about the Brandybucks and their connection to the Old Forest."},{"name":"Stranger from Michel Delving","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Michel Delving","description":"Visitor from the Westfarthing who speculated about Bilbo's treasure.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Talked about Bilbo's rumored tunnels and wealth."},{"name":"Sackville-Bagginses","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Family of hobbits who scowled at Bilbo's announcement.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed in wrath after Bilbo's disappearance."},{"name":"Old Odo Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Hobbit with large, furry feet who commented on Bilbo's disappearance.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Suspected Bilbo's disappearance was not a prank."},{"name":"Adelard Took","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Recipient of an umbrella labeled 'For Adelard Took, for his VERY OWN, from Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an umbrella from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Dora Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Drogo’s sister and the eldest surviving female relative of Bilbo and Frodo; ninety-nine years old.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a waste-paper basket labeled 'For Dora Baggins in memory of a LONG correspondence'."},{"name":"Milo Burrows","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Recipient of a gold pen and ink-bottle labeled 'For Milo Burrows, hoping it will be useful, from B.B'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a gold pen and ink-bottle from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Angelica","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A young Baggins who received a round convex mirror labeled 'For Angelica’s use, from Uncle Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a mirror from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Hugo Bracegirdle","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A collector of books who received an empty book-case labeled 'For the collection of Hugo Bracegirdle'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an 