 rumored tunnels and wealth."},{"name":"Sackville-Bagginses","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Family of hobbits who scowled at Bilbo's announcement.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed in wrath after Bilbo's disappearance."},{"name":"Old Odo Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Hobbit with large, furry feet who commented on Bilbo's disappearance.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Suspected Bilbo's disappearance was not a prank."},{"name":"Adelard Took","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Recipient of an umbrella labeled 'For Adelard Took, for his VERY OWN, from Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an umbrella from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Dora Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Drogo’s sister and the eldest surviving female relative of Bilbo and Frodo; ninety-nine years old.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a waste-paper basket labeled 'For Dora Baggins in memory of a LONG correspondence'."},{"name":"Milo Burrows","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Recipient of a gold pen and ink-bottle labeled 'For Milo Burrows, hoping it will be useful, from B.B'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a gold pen and ink-bottle from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Angelica","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A young Baggins who received a round convex mirror labeled 'For Angelica’s use, from Uncle Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a mirror from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Hugo Bracegirdle","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A collector of books who received an empty book-case labeled 'For the collection of Hugo Bracegirdle'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an empty book-case from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s relative who took silver spoons labeled 'For Lobelia Sackville-Baggins, as a PRESENT'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over spoons and left with them."},{"name":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s heir (before Frodo’s adoption) who demanded to see Frodo’s will.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over the will and left in frustration."},{"name":"Sancho Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Old Odo Proudfoot’s grandson who excavated the pantry seeking Bilbo’s gold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Attempted to excavate the pantry and was ejected by Frodo."},{"name":"Merry Brandybuck","aliases":["Master of Buckland"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 10: STRIDER","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A Brandybuck heir who becomes Frodo's companion on his journey.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Companion"}],"recentEvents":"Reported seeing Black Riders, discussed Black Breath, and helped set up disguises"},{"name":"