obbit with large, furry feet who commented on Bilbo's disappearance.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Suspected Bilbo's disappearance was not a prank."},{"name":"Adelard Took","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Recipient of an umbrella labeled 'For Adelard Took, for his VERY OWN, from Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an umbrella from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Dora Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Drogo’s sister and the eldest surviving female relative of Bilbo and Frodo; ninety-nine years old.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a waste-paper basket labeled 'For Dora Baggins in memory of a LONG correspondence'."},{"name":"Milo Burrows","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Recipient of a gold pen and ink-bottle labeled 'For Milo Burrows, hoping it will be useful, from B.B'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a gold pen and ink-bottle from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Angelica","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A young Baggins who received a round convex mirror labeled 'For Angelica’s use, from Uncle Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a mirror from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Hugo Bracegirdle","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A collector of books who received an empty book-case labeled 'For the collection of Hugo Bracegirdle'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an empty book-case from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s relative who took silver spoons labeled 'For Lobelia Sackville-Baggins, as a PRESENT'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over spoons and left with them."},{"name":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s heir (before Frodo’s adoption) who demanded to see Frodo’s will.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over the will and left in frustration."},{"name":"Sancho Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Old Odo Proudfoot’s grandson who excavated the pantry seeking Bilbo’s gold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Attempted to excavate the pantry and was ejected by Frodo."},{"name":"Merry Brandybuck","aliases":["Master of Buckland","Merry"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 10: THE VOICE OF SARUMAN","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A hobbit who joined the company of the Ring and was presumed lost but was found feasting in Isengard","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Close friend and companion"},{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Met and conversed with during their journey"},{"character":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Gimli son of Glóin","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Legolas Greenleaf","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the dialogue with Saruman"},{"name":"Ted Sandyman","aliases":["Sandyman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE SHADOW OF THE PAST","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A miller's son who engaged in conversation with Sam Gamgee about rumors of strange events in the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Neighbor"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in a discussion at The Green Dragon about rumors of elves, giants, and dragons."},{"name":"Déagol","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE SHADOW OF THE PAST","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A hobbit who discovered the One Ring but was murdered by Sméagol.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by Sméagol after being robbed of the Ring."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Strider","Aragorn","Aragorn [Strider]"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 10: THE VOICE OF SARUMAN","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"Leader of the Company, bearing the sword Andúril, guides the group through the dale and towards Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf the Grey","relationship":"Advisor and companion"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Companion and leader of the quest"},{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Companion and friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Companion and friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Companion and friend"},{"character":"Glorfindel","relationship":"Allied warrior"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Advisor"},{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"Love interest"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Companion and fellow traveler"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Traveling companion"},{"character":"Gimli son of Glóin","relationship":"Companion and friend"},{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Recipient of the Elfstone brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Éomer son of Éomund","relationship":"Negotiating for passage through Rohan"},{"character":"Théoden son of Thengel","relationship":"King of the Mark"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Affianc