 ink-bottle from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Angelica","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A young Baggins who received a round convex mirror labeled 'For Angelica’s use, from Uncle Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a mirror from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Hugo Bracegirdle","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A collector of books who received an empty book-case labeled 'For the collection of Hugo Bracegirdle'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an empty book-case from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s relative who took silver spoons labeled 'For Lobelia Sackville-Baggins, as a PRESENT'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over spoons and left with them."},{"name":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s heir (before Frodo’s adoption) who demanded to see Frodo’s will.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over the will and left in frustration."},{"name":"Sancho Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Old Odo Proudfoot’s grandson who excavated the pantry seeking Bilbo’s gold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Attempted to excavate the pantry and was ejected by Frodo."},{"name":"Merry Brandybuck","aliases":["Master of Buckland","Merry"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 11: THE PALANTÍR","currentLocation":"En route to Helm’s Deep","description":"A hobbit who joined the company of the Ring and was presumed lost but was found feasting in Isengard","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Close friend and companion"},{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Met and conversed with during their journey"},{"character":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Gimli son of Glóin","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Legolas Greenleaf","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Cousin"},{"character":"Gandalf the White","relationship":"Mentor and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Pippin about meddling with Wizards' affairs and discussed the group's route"},{"name":"Ted Sandyman","aliases":["Sandyman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE SHADOW OF THE PAST","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A miller's son who engaged in conversation with Sam Gamgee about rumors of strange events in the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Neighbor"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in a discussion at The Green Dragon about rumors of elves, giants, and dragons."},{"name":"Déagol","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE SHADOW OF THE PAST","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A hobbit who discovered the One Ring but was murdered by Sméagol.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by Sméagol after being robbed of the Ring."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Strider","Aragorn","Aragorn [Strider]"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3: THE BLACK GATE IS CLOSED","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"Leader of the Company, bearing the sword Andúril, guides the group through the dale and towards Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf the Grey","relationship":"Advisor and companion"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Companion and leader of