mpanion and protector"},{"character":"Fro,do Baggins","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Gandalf the Grey","relationship":"Advisor"},{"character":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Companion and friend"},{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Recipient of a silver belt"},{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Met and conversed with during their journey"},{"character":"Gimli son of Glóin","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Legolas Greenleaf","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Cousin"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Mentor"},{"character":"Gandalf the White","relationship":"Mentor and guardian"}],"recentEvents":"Conversation with Gandalf about the Palantír, Nazgûl, and the journey"},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Black Rider"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4: TREEBEARD","currentLocation":"River Ford","description":"A tall, dark-cloaked figure pursued Frodo and his companions. Spoke in a strange manner and exhibited unusual sensory abilities.","relationships":[{"character":"Farmer Maggot","relationship":"Encountered"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Pursued"}],"recentEvents":"Continued pursuit of the hobbits through the forest"},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3: THREE IS COMPANY","currentLocation":"Green hall","description":"Leader of a group of Elves who encountered Frodo and his companions. Identified himself as of the House of Finrod.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Advisor and conversant"}],"recentEvents":"Advised Frodo to flee the Shire, warned of the Black Riders, and encouraged him to seek Gandalf's counsel."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":