tLocation":"Road to Isengard","description":"Lord of Westfold, arrived with reinforcements during the battle","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","relationship":"Allied commander"},{"character":"Théoden son of Thengel","relationship":"Allied"}],"recentEvents":"Leading the Men of the Mark, overseeing the handling of Dunland captives"},{"name":"Isengard","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter 8: THE ROAD TO ISENGARD","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"The ruined stronghold of Saruman, now under the control of the Ents","relationships":[]},{"name":"Men from the South","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3: THE BLACK GATE IS CLOSED","currentLocation":"Near the Black Gate","description":"Warriors in red and gold, bearing round shields and spears with red tips","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Observed by Gollum and Sam, described as approaching Mordor"},{"name":"Faramir","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: JOURNEY TO THE CROSS-ROADS","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"Captain of Gondor, known for his wisdom and honor, engages in deep conversation with Frodo and Sam about the Ring and his brother Boromir.","relationships":[{"character":"Mablung","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Damrod","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Suspects Frodo of hiding the Ring’s history"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who died under mysterious circumstances"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Respected companion"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Warned about the creature's dangers"},{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Mentor figure"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned by Sam regarding his instruction to avoid drinking water in Morgul."},{"name":"Mablung","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 5: THE WINDOW ON THE WEST","currentLocation":"Ithi