"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Rescuer of"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Rescuer of"}],"recentEvents":"Rescued Frodo, Sam, Pippin, and Merry from Barrow-wights, defeated a Barrow-wight"},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: IN THE HOUSE OF TOM BOMBADIL","currentLocation":"Old Forest","description":"A sentient willow tree with a cunning and malevolent nature, feared by the forest creatures.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Antagonist"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed by Tom Bombadil as a dangerous entity in the forest."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["River-daughter"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: IN THE HOUSE OF TOM BOMBADIL","currentLocation":"Old Forest","description":"Daughter of the River, wife of Tom Bombadil, and a figure of serene beauty and mystery.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"}],"recentEvents":"Sang songs to Frodo and Sam, prepared food, and assisted in setting the table."},{"name":"Barrow-wight","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 8: FOG ON THE BARROW-DOWNS","currentLocation":"Barrow-downs","description":"Malevolent spirit that captured the hobbits and was defeated by Tom Bombadil","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Defeated by"}],"recentEvents":"Captured Frodo, Sam, Pippin, and Merry; defeated by Tom Bombadil"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 10: STRIDER","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"Member of the Butterbur family, helped set up disguises","relationships":[{"character":"Barliman Butterbur","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"The Butterbur Family","relationship":"Part of"}],"recentEvents":"Assisted in preparing disguises and reported on Black Riders' movements"},{"name":"Gatekeeper","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","