hip":"Brother who died under mysterious circumstances"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Respected companion"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Warned about the creature's dangers"},{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Mentor figure"}],"recentEvents":"Return to Minas Tirith"},{"name":"Mablung","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 5: THE WINDOW ON THE WEST","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"Gondor soldier accompanying Faramir and Frodo","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Comrade in Gondor’s forces"},{"character":"Damrod","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guardian during the interrogation"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the secret camp setup with Faramir and Damrod"},{"name":"Damrod","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 5: THE WINDOW ON THE WEST","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"Soldier of Gondor, Ranger of Ithilien, spoke in elven-tongue","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Comrade in Gondor’s forces"},{"character":"Mablung","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guardian during the interrogation"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the secret camp setup with Faram, Mablung, and Frodo"},{"name":"Mûmak","aliases":["Oliphaunt"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4: OF HERBS AND STEWED RABBIT","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A massive creature of Harad, part of the battle","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Southrons"},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 10: THE CHOICES OF MASTER SAMWISE","currentLocation":"Near Cirith Ungol","description":"Frodo's loyal gardener and companion, carrying provisions and providing support.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Companion and Ring-bearer"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Respects Faramir’s authority but challenges his accusations"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Fighting"}],"recentEvents":"Fought Orcs to save Frodo, discovered Frodo was alive but captured"},{"name":"Anborn","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6: THE FORBIDDEN POOL","currentLocation":"Henneth Annûn","description":"A scout under Faramir's command, reports unusual sightings in the wilderness.","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Ordered to escort Gollum"}],"recentEvents":"Took Gollum away from Frodo and Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 9: SHELOB’S LAIR","currentLocation":"Shelob’s Lair (Torech Ungol)","description":"A giant spider and predator, dwells in the dark tunnels near Cirith Ungol.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Attacking"}],"recentEvents":"Chased Frodo down the path, nearly capturing him"},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: MINAS TIRITH","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Steward of Gondor, ruler of Minas Tirith, engaged in political and military strategy","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf the White","relationship":"Advisor and correspondent"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Father (deceased)"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Father figure figure/ally"}],"recentEvents":"Summoned Pippin"},{"name":"Ingold","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: MINAS TIRITH","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Leader of the guards at the gates of Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf the White","relationship":"Interacted with during Pippin's entry"}],"recentEvents":"Checked Pippin's identity, allowed him and Gandalf to enter Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Beregond son of Baranor","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: MINAS TIRITH","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Guardian of Minas Tirith, tasked with instructing Pippin in pass-words","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Guardian and companion"},{"character":"Bergil son of Beregond","relationship":"son"}],"recentEvents":"Welcomed Pippin, summoned him to Denethor"},{"name":"Bergil son of Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: MINAS TIRITH","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A son of Beregond, part of the companies entering Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Companion and guide"},{"character":"Beregond son of Baranor","relationship":"father"}],"recentEvents":"Parted with Pippin, summoned to Denethor"}],"locations":[{"name":"The Shire","aliases":["Shire of the Hobbits","Bag End","Bagshot Row"],"arc":"The Company of the Ring's Formation","description":"A fertile region in Eriador where Hobbits live in peace, known for its well-ordered farms and communities.","recentEvents":"Frodo Baggins is managing the aftermath of Bilbo's departure, dealing with visitors and chaos at Bag End.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Adjacent region to the east"},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Historical homeland of Hobbits before settling in the Shire"}]},{"name":"Bree","aliases":["Bree-land"],"arc":"Aragorn's Leadership and the Quest's Legacy","description":"A key crossroads town in Eriador, home to the Butterbur family and a hub for travelers.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as the origin of pipe-weed smoking and a center for trade and news.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Eastward neighbor"},{"location":"The Prancing Pony","relationship":"Home of the inn"}]},{"name":"Brandywine Bridge","aliases":["Bridge of Stonebows"],"description":"A historic crossing over the Brandywine River, marking the start of the Shire-reckoning.","recentEvents":"Site of the Hobbits' migration and the beginning of their recorded history.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Border landmark"},{"location":"Fornost","relationship":"Previously under the rule of the North Kingdom"}]},{"name":"Rivendell","aliases":["Elven realm"],"arc":"Aragorn's Leadership and the Quest's Legacy","description":"A hidden Elven stronghold in the foothills of the Misty Mountains, a center of wisdom and refuge.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as the original homeland of Hobbits before their migration.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Historical connection"},{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Located nearby"}]},{"name":"Misty Mountains","aliases":["Misty Mountains"],"description":"A vast mountain range separating Eriador from the western lands, home to ancient secrets.","recentEvents":"Site of the Hobbits' migration and the shadow that darkened Greenwood.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Geographical barrier"},{"location":"Mirkwood","relationship":"Formerly known as Greenwood the Great"}]},{"name":"Grey Havens","aliases":["West of the Sea"],"description":"A coastal region in the west where Elves reside, marking the edge of the known world.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a place of mystery and the Elves' departure from Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Westernmost point of Hobbit lands"}]},{"name":"Chetwood","aliases":["Chetwood"],"description":"A forested region surrounding Bree, part of the ancient Wilderland.","recentEvents":"Home to early Hobbit settlements and a place of transition for migrating Hobbits.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Surrounding forest"}]},{"name":"Longbottom","aliases":["Southfarthing"],"description":"A region in the southern part of the Shire known for its fertile lands and pipe-weed cultivation.","recentEvents":"Origin of the pipe-weed plant and a key area for Hobbit agriculture.","relationships":[{"location":"The Sh,ire","relationship":"Southern district"}]},{"name":"Marish","aliases":["Eastfarthing"],"description":"A low-lying, marshy region of the Shire inhabited by Stoors and known for its unique dialect.","recentEvents":"Home to the Eastfarthing Hobbits and a site of early Hobbit settlement.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Eastern district"}]},{"name":"White Downs","aliases":["Downs"],"arc":"Aragorn's Leadership, Rohirrim Alliance, and the Quest's Legacy","description":"A hill region in the Shire where the chief township of Michel Delving is located.","recentEvents":"The group rested here after a long march, discovering Orc footprints and a hobbit's trail leading north.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Key hill region"},{"location":"Rohan","relationship":"Central feature of the landscape"},{"location":"Entwash Vale","relationship":"Adjacent to the southern edge"}]},{"name":"Old Forest","aliases":["Old Forest"],"arc":"The Shire's Hidden Secrets and Transition","description":"A dark, foreboding woodland adjacent to the Brandywine River, known for its eerie reputation.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where the Brandybucks live, with rumors of strange occurrences.","relationships":[{"location":"Brandywine Bridge","relationship":"Adjacent to the river"}]},{"name":"Michel Delving","aliases":["Michel Delving"],"description":"A town in the Westfarthing, known as the home of the stranger who comments on Bilbo's wealth.","recentEvents":"A visitor from this town speculates about Bilbo's hidden treasures.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Part of the broader region"}]},{"name":"Esgaroth","aliases":["Lake-town"],"description":"A city on the Long Lake, known for its grandeur and the meeting place of the Dwarves.","recentEvents":"Bilbo Baggins mentions arriving there by barrel on his birthday.","relationships":[{"location":"Long Lake","relationship":"situated on"}]},{"name":"Long Lake","description":"A large body of water in the region, with Esgaroth situated on its shores.","recentEvents":"Bilbo Baggins arrived there by barrel on his birthday.","relationships":[{"location":"Esgaroth","relationship":"situated on"}]},{"name":"Bywater","arc":"The Shire's Transition and External Threats","description":"A village in the Shire known for its waterways and the home of the Gamgees.","recentEvents":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins confronts Frodo, and Old Noakes and others receive gifts.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Part of"}],"parentLocation":"The Shire"},{"name":"Blue Mountains","aliases":["Blue Mountains"],"description":"Mountain range in the East where dwarves mine and seek refuge.","recentEvents":"Dwarves travel through the Shire en route to their mines, seeking refuge from the Enemy's influence.","relationships":[{"location":"East-West Road","relationship":"Connected by the ancient trade route"}]},{"name":"North Moors","aliases":["North Moors"],"description":"Wild, treeless region north of the Shire known for eerie sightings.","recentEvents":"Hobbits report seeing a giant Tree-man walking beyond the North Moors.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"Adjacent territory with border disputes"}]},{"name":"White Towers","aliases":["White Towers"],"description":"Ancient fortresses west of the Shire, once home to elven refugees.","recentEvents":"Elven ships depart from Grey Havens, passing the White Towers en route to the West.","relationships":[{"location":"Grey Havens","relationship":"Part of the western maritime route"}]},{"name":"Gladden Fields","description":"A river valley where Isildur was waylaid by Orcs, leading to the loss of the One Ring.","recentEvents":"The One Ring fell into the Great River Anduin here after Isildur's death.","relationships":[{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Source of the stream that flows through the Gladden Fields"},{"location":"Great River Anduin","relationship":"The river where the One Ring fell into after Isildur's death"}]},{"name":"Mordor","aliases":["Land of Mordor"],"arc":"Rohan's Defense and Strategic Movements","description":"A dark, volcanic region dominated by Sauron's forces, central to the Ring's threat.","recentEvents":"Gollum is heading to Mordor, where the Dark Power seeks to reclaim the Ring.","relationships":[{"location":"Orodruin","relationship":"Contains the Cracks of Doom"},{"location":"Wilderland","relationship":"Gollum traveled south through this region"}]},{"name":"Wilderland","description":"A vast, untamed region stretching across Middle-earth, home to many hidden paths.","recentEvents":"Aragorn and Gandalf searched for Gollum without success through this area.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Northwestern border region"}]},{"name":"Orodruin","aliases":["Fire-mountain"],"description":"A volcanic mountain where the One Ring must be destroyed, known for its fiery depths.","recentEvents":"Gandalf reveals the only way to destroy the Ring is by casting it into the Cracks of Doom here.","relationships":[{"location":"Cracks of Doom","relationship":"Contains the destructive fissures"}]},{"name":"Cracks of Doom","description":"The volcanic fissures within Orodruin where the One Ring is destined to be destroyed.","recentEvents":"Frodo contemplates casting the Ring into these deadly chasms to end its power.","relationships":[{"location":"Orodruin","relationship":"Located within the Fire-mountain"}]},{"name":"Green Hill Country","aliases":["Green Hills"],"description":"A region in the Eastfarthing, known for its rolling hills and proximity to the Brandywine River.","recentEvents":"Frodo, Sam, and Pippin passed through this area en route to Buckland, camping in its woods.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Part of the Shire's eastern borders"},{"location":"Woody End","relationship":"Adjacent wild corner of the Eastfarthing"}]},{"name":"Woody End","description":"A secluded, wild corner of the Eastfarthing, characterized by dense forests and rugged terrain.","recentEvents":"The group camped in the fir-wood near Woody End after crossing the Brandywine River.","relationships":[{"location":"Green Hill Country","relationship":"Part of the Green Hill Country region"}]},{"name":"Woodhall","aliases":["Woodhall"],"description":"A village in the Shire located near the Brandywine River, known for its ancient oak-trees and proximity to the Woody End.","recentEvents":"Frodo, Sam, and Pippin were led by Elves to this village after encountering a Black Rider on the road. The Elves camped here overnight, sharing songs and stories.","relationships":[{"location":"Woody End","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Brandywine River","relationship":"Nearby landmark"}]},{"name":"Bucklebury Ferry","aliases":["Ferry lane"],"description":"A critical crossing point in the Shire, connecting the western regions to the Brandywine River.","recentEvents":"Frodo, Sam, Pippin, and Farmer Maggot arrive here after a tense journey, narrowly avoiding a Black Rider.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Key transportation hub"},{"location":"Marish","relationship":"Adjacent"},{"location":"Stock","relationship":"Linked via the Ferry lane"}],"parentLocation":"The Shire"},{"name":"Stock-brook","aliases":["Stock Brook","Stock"],"description":"A village near Bucklebury in the Shire, known for its proximity to the Ferry lane.","recentEvents":"Frodo and his companions travel through Stock on their way to the Bucklebury Ferry, encountering a Black Rider and Farmer Maggot's assistance.","relationships":[{"location":"Marish","relationship":"Part of"},{"location":"Stock","relationship":"Flows through"},{"location":"Bucklebury Ferry","relationship":"Adjacent to the Ferry lane"},{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Part of the Shire's rural landscape"}],"parentLocation":"Marish"},{"name":"Bamfurlong","aliases":["Bamfurlong Farm"],"description":"Farmer Maggot's farm, a notable landmark in the Marish region.","recentEvents":"Frodo's group encounters Maggot's dogs and learns about a mysterious black rider seeking Baggins.","relationships":[{"location":"Marish","relationship":"Part of"},{"location":"Stock","relationship":"Nearby"}],"parentLocation":"Marish"},{"name":"High Hay","aliases":["The Hedge"],"description":"A tall, thick hedge protecting Buckland from eastern threats, meticulously maintained by the Bucklanders.","recentEvents":"The group passed through High Hay while traveling from the Brandywine River to Buckland, noting its role in shielding the region.","relationships":[{"location":"Buckland","relationship":"Defensive barrier"},{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Shares a border with the hedge"}]},{"name":"Buckland","aliases":["Buckland Region"],"description":"A fertile region in the Shire known for its rolling hills and proximity to the Brandywine River.","recentEvents":"Frodo and his companions plan to leave Buckland to evade the Black Riders, using the Old Forest as a route.","relationships":[{"location":"North-gate","relationship":"Buckland's northern boundary"},{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Part of the Shire region"}]},{"name":"North-gate","aliases":["Buckland's North-gate"],"description":"A key entry point to Buckland, guarded by hedge and riverbank defenses.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a potential bottleneck for the Black Riders, though its effectiveness is uncertain.","relationships":[{"location":"Buckland","relationship":"Northern boundary"},{"location":"Brandywine Bridge","relationship":"Adjacent to the riverbank"}]},{"name":"Bonfire Glade","aliases":["Bonfire Clearing"],"description":"A circular clearing in the Old Forest where a bonfire was once made by hobbits to repel attacking trees.","recentEvents":"The hobbits passed through this glade after emerging from the tunnel under the Hedge, finding temporary respite from the forest's oppressive presence.","relationships":[{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Part of"}],"parentLocation":"Old Forest"},{"name":"Withywindle River","aliases":["Withywindle"],"description":"A river flowing through the Old Forest, noted for its winding path and the willow trees lining its banks.","recentEvents":"The hobbits followed a path along its banks, eventually reaching a wide stretch where they encountered a large willow tree and rested.","relationships":[{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Runs through"}]},{"name":"Greenway","aliases":["North Road"],"description":"An ancient road once used for trade, now overgrown and abandoned.","recentEvents":"Frodo and his companions arrive at the Greenway-crossing, entering Bree-land.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Bordering region"}]},{"name":"Greenway-crossing","description":"The point where the Greenway meets the Road, marking entry into Bree-land.","recentEvents":"The hobbits arrive here, prompting suspicion from the gatekeeper.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Entry point"}]},{"name":"Weathertop","aliases":["Weathertop Hill"],"arc":"Frodo's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"A prominent hill with a conical peak, offering a commanding view of the surrounding wilderness and the Old Road.","recentEvents":"Frodo and the hobbits are attacked by Black Riders under the cover of darkness. Frodo resists the Ring's temptation and is wounded.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"North of Bree, halfway to Rivendell"},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Linked through Elrond's lineage and the Silmaril legend"},{"location":"Old Road","relationship":"The Old Road runs south of Weathertop, a key route the group aims to bypass"},{"location":"Midgewater Marshes","relationship":"Lies to the west, with the group emerging from the marshes toward this hill"},{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Adjacent region where the group seeks shelter"}]},{"name":"Midgewater Marshes","aliases":["Midgewater"],"description":"A vast, treacherous wetland stretching east of Bree-land, known for its shifting quagmires and biting insects.","recentEvents":"The hobbits traversed the marshes, facing dangerous terrain and relentless midges, while Strider plotted their route to Weathertop.","relationships":[{"location":"Chetwood","relationship":"Lies to the west, from which the group departed"},{"location":"Weathertop","relationship":"Lies to the east, the next major landmark in their journey"}]},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","aliases":["Bruinen Ford","Loudwater","Loudwater River"],"arc":"Frodo's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"A river crossing point near the Road, guarded by ancient ruins and associated with the Bruinen's turbulent waters.","recentEvents":"Strider identifies the Loudwater as the river crossed at the Ford of Bruinen, critical for navigating toward Rivendell.","relationships":[{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"The Loudwater river flows out of Rivendell, with the Ford of Bruinen marking its crossing point"},{"location":"Road","relationship":"Linked to the crossing route"},{"location":"Ettendales","relationship":"Located in the northern hills"},{"location":"Weathertop","relationship":"The Road passes near Weathertop before reaching the Loudwater"}]},{"name":"Sundering Seas","aliases":["Sundering Seas"],"description":"A vast body of water separating Middle-earth from the Undying Lands, mentioned in Elven lore.","recentEvents":"Referenced in Strider's song about Beren and Lúthien's mythic tale of love and sacrifice.","relationships":[{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Symbolically tied to Elrond's kinship with Lúthien's lineage"}]},{"name":"Neldoreth","aliases":["Neldoreth"],"description":"A hidden forest kingdom in the Blue Mountains, home to Thingol and the Silmarils.","recentEvents":"Mentioned in the legend of Beren and Lúthien's elven romance and their battle against Morgoth.","relationships":[{"location":"Blue Mountains","relationship":"Part of the mountain range"},{"location":"Esgalduin","relationship":"Adjacent to the enchanted river"}]},{"name":"Esgalduin","aliases":["Esgalduin"],"description":"An enchanted river flowing through the forest of Neldoreth, associated with Elven magic.","recentEvents":"Featured in the legend of Lúthien's song and the Silmaril's journey.","relationships":[{"location":"Neldoreth","relationship":"Flows through the forest kingdom"}]},{"name":"River Hoarwell","aliases":["Mitheithel"],"description":"A river flowing from the Ettenmoors, joining the Loudwater in the South.","recentEvents":"Frodo's group crossed this river via the Last Bridge, finding an elf-stone as a sign of safe passage.","relationships":[{"location":"Ettenmoors","relationship":"Source of the river"},{"location":"Road","relationship":"Crossed via the Last Bridge"}]},{"name":"Last Bridge","description":"A stone bridge spanning the River Hoarwell, where the Road crosses.","recentEvents":"Strider discovered an elf-stone here, indicating the Black Riders had not followed them.","relationships":[{"location":"River Hoarwell","relationship":"Crossing point"},{"location":"Road","relationship":"Key junction"}]},{"name":"Bridge of Mitheithel","aliases":["Mitheithel Bridge"],"description":"A stone bridge spanning a river, marked by a token left by Glorfindel.","recentEvents":"Glorfindel left a token here seven days prior, which the group found as they pursued the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"location":"Ford of Bruinen","relationship":"Lies downstream along the same river"}]},{"name":"Baranduin","aliases":["Baranduin River"],"description":"A river crossing where Glorfindel's search party encountered enemies.","recentEvents":"Glorfindel crossed this river to track the group, evading three servants of Sauron.","relationships":[{"location":"Bridge of Mitheithel","relationship":"Flowing through the same region"}]},{"name":"Hall of Fire","aliases":["Fire Hall"],"description":"A grand hall within Rivendell with a central hearth and carven pillars, serving as a gathering place for reflection and storytelling.","recentEvents":"Frodo and others gather here after the feast; Bilbo's songwriting session occurs here with Strider's involvement.","relationships":[{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Contained within"}]},{"name":"Dead Marshes","aliases":["Dead Marshes"],"arc":"Frodo's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"A treacherous wetland area near the Anduin River, known for its eerie atmosphere and dangers.","recentEvents":"Aragorn tracks Gollum through the Dead Marshes, following his trail toward Mirkwood.","relationships":[{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Located to the north, with the Dead Marshes lying between them and the Anduin"},{"location":"Ford of Bruinen","relationship":"Adjacent to the Dead Marshes, where the Black Riders are active"}]},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","aliases":["Rohan Pass"],"arc":"Ents' War Against Isengard and Rohan's Strategic Position","description":"A narrow pass between the Misty Mountains and the White Mountains (Ered Nimrais), serving as a strategic crossing point.","recentEvents":"Saruman's forces are mustering here, and Gandalf travels through it on his way to Rohan.","relationships":[{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Adjacent to the eastern side"},{"location":"White Mountains","relationship":"Adjacent to the western side"}]},{"name":"Riddermark","aliases":["Rohan"],"description":"The kingdom of the Rohirrim, a horse-riding people known for their martial prowess and loyalty to the king.","recentEvents":"Éomer's company departed this land to pursue the group, lending them horses for their journey.","relationships":[{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Borders the eastern region"},{"location":"White Mountains","relationship":"Borders the western region"},{"location":"Rohan","relationship":"Canonical name for the region"},{"location":"White Downs","relationship":"Adjacent to the Riddermark"},{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Heartland of the kingdom"},{"location":"Entwash","relationship":"Borders the northern edge of the realm"}]},{"name":"Golden Hall","aliases":["Rohan's capital","Hall of Théoden","Edoras","Meduseld"],"arc":"Rohan's Defense and the War Against Isengard","description":"The capital of the Rohirrim, where Théoden resides and the impending battle against Saruman's forces is set to unfold.","recentEvents":"Théoden announces Éowyn as leader of the Eorlingas, gifts her a sword, and departs with the Rohirrim to battle. Gandalf receives Shadowfax, and the host rides west.","relationships":[{"location":"Rohan","relationship":"Central location within the kingdom"},{"location":"Entwade","relationship":"Accessible via the river's southern bank"},{"location":"Fangorn Forest","relationship":"Separated by the Entwash Vale"},{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"Geographically distant but strategically linked through the war between Rohan and Saruman"},{"location":"White Mountains","relationship":"Located under the slopes of the White Mountains"},{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Part of the city"},{"location":"Dunharrow","relationship":"Refuge for survivors if the battle goes ill"}]},{"name":"Ettenmoors","description":"A mountainous region traversed by Gandalf during his journey from Bree to Rivendell","recentEvents":"Scouts explored the Ettenmoors, finding no trace of the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Connected via the Road"},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Connected via the Road"},{"location":"Hoarwell River","relationship":"Adjacent to"}]},{"name":"Tharbad","aliases":["Old North Road Crossing"],"description":"A ruined town where the North Road crosses the Greyflood River.","recentEvents":"Scouts reached Tharbad during their westward search, confirming no signs of the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"location":"Greyflood","relationship":"Crossed by the North Road"},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Scouted from"}]},{"name":"Rhosgobel","description":"A forested region in Wilderland where Radagast the Brown once resided.","recentEvents":"Scouts passed through Rhosgobel, finding it abandoned and searching for Radagast.","relationships":[{"location":"Wilderland","relationship":"Part of"},{"location":"Mirkwood","relationship":"Adjacent to"}],"parentLocation":"Wilderland"},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","arc":"The Company of the Ring's Formation","description":"A high mountain pass through the Misty Mountains, leading into Wilderland.","recentEvents":"Scouts traversed the Redhorn Gate on their journey southward.","relationships":[{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Pass through"},{"location":"Wilderland","relationship":"Entrance to"}]},{"name":"Silverlode River","aliases":["Silverlode"],"description":"A cold, icy river rising from the depths of the Misty Mountains, known for its crystalline waters and hidden springs.","recentEvents":"The Company approached its source in the mountains, with Gimli recalling its springs and its connection to the Dwarves' ancient lands.","relationships":[{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Rises from the northern slopes"}]},{"name":"Mirrormere","aliases":["Mirrormere"],"description":"A secluded glacial basin in the heart of the Misty Mountains where the Silverlode River originates, shrouded in mystery and ancient Dwarven lore.","recentEvents":"The Company's path led them toward its icy springs, though they did not yet reach it, as the journey through the mountains intensified.","relationships":[{"location":"Silverlode River","relationship":"Site of the river's origin"},{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"A hidden valley within the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Stair Falls","aliases":["Sirannon Falls"],"description":"A former waterfall where the Sirannon stream flowed before being dammed, now a dry ravine with crumbling stone steps.","recentEvents":"The group discovered the Stair Falls, where the Sirannon stream once flowed, but now the water is diverted, leaving only a dry channel.","relationships":[{"location":"Moria","relationship":"The Stair Falls marks the western approach to Moria's entrance, where the ancient road once met the stream."},{"location":"Sirannon","relationship":"The Stair Falls is the site where the Sirannon stream originally flowed before being dammed."}]},{"name":"Sirannon Lake","aliases":["Dammed Sirannon"],"description":"A vast, stagnant lake formed by the damming of the Sirannon stream, blocking the path to Moria.","recentEvents":"The group encountered the lake, which has rendered the ancient road impassable, forcing them to seek an alternative route around the northern edge.","relationships":[{"location":"Moria","relationship":"The lake blocks the direct path to Moria, requiring the Company to circumvent it."},{"location":"Stair Falls","relationship":"The lake was created by damming the Sirannon stream at the Stair Falls."}]},{"name":"West-door","aliases":["West Door"],"description":"The entrance to the Mines of Moria, marked by ancient Elven carvings and the Doors of Durin.","recentEvents":"Gandalf and the Company discovered and opened the West-door using the Elvish word 'Mellon' (Friend). The doors closed behind them, blocking their path back.","relationships":[{"location":"Mines of Moria","relationship":"Entrance"}]},{"name":"East-gate","aliases":["East Gate"],"description":"The exit from the Mines of Moria, located at the eastern end of the labyrinthine tunnels.","recentEvents":"The group is traveling toward the East-gate, though the path is perilous and obscured by darkness and dangers.","relationships":[{"location":"Mines of Moria","relationship":"Exit"}]},{"name":"Bridge of Khazad-dûm","aliases":["Khazad-dûm Bridge"],"description":"A stone bridge spanning a chasm in the depths of Moria, serving as the final exit from the mines.","recentEvents":"The Company of the Ring narrowly escapes through the bridge after a battle with orcs and a cave troll, with Gandalf sacrificing himself to block pursuers.","relationships":[{"location":"Moria","relationship":"Part of the mines' complex structure"},{"location":"First Deep","relationship":"Located on the level below the Gates"}]},{"name":"First Deep","description":"The lowest level of Moria, where the Company takes refuge after escaping the upper halls, now engulfed in fire.","recentEvents":"The group descends into the First Deep, where they encounter flames and pursue the pursuing orcs, eventually reaching the Bridge of Khazad-dûm.","relationships":[{"location":"Moria","relationship":"A level within the mines"},{"location":"Silverlode River","relationship":"Located near the eastern exit of the mines"}]},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","aliases":["Dimrill Dale"],"description":"A valley located east of the Misty Mountains, where the group emerges after escaping the Mines of Moria.","recentEvents":"The Fellowship escapes the Mines of Moria after Gandalf's sacrifice, emerging into Dimrill Dale. The group weeps for Gandalf's death as the drumbeats of the Dead Marshes fade.","relationships":[{"location":"Moria","relationship":"Beyond the Great Gates"}]},{"name":"Lothlórien","aliases":["Golden Wood"],"arc":"Aragorn's Leadership and the Quest's Legacy","description":"A vast, enchanted woodland realm in Middle-earth, home to the Elves of the Silvan kindred. Its trees glow with an otherworldly light, and its rivers shimmer with magic.","recentEvents":"The Company approaches the borders of Lothlórien after escaping Moria. They rest by the Nimrodel stream and hear a song about the region's tragic history.","relationships":[{"location":"Silverlode River","relationship":"Flows into Lothlórien"},{"location":"Mirrormere","relationship":"Located in the northern glen of the Misty Mountains"}]},{"name":"Nimrodel","aliases":["Nimrodel Stream"],"description":"A clear, healing stream that flows through Lothlórien, known for its rainbow falls and golden flowers. It joins the Silverlode River.","recentEvents":"The Company wades across Nimrodel, where Legolas sings a melancholic tale of its tragic past and the Elves' sorrow.","relationships":[{"location":"Silverlode River","relationship":"Converges with the Silverlode"},{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"A tributary within the Golden Wood"}]},{"name":"Naith of Lórien","aliases":["Gore"],"description":"A narrow landmass between the Silverlode River and the Great River Anduin, forming a spearhead-shaped corridor through Lothlórien.","recentEvents":"The Company traversed this region blindfolded under Elven guard, avoiding Orc scouts and navigating Elven-controlled territory.","relationships":[{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"Part of"},{"location":"Silverlode River","relationship":"Borders"}],"parentLocation":"Lothlórien"},{"name":"Caras Galadhon","aliases":["City of the Galadhrim"],"description":"The capital of Lothlórien, a vast green city encircling a hill with mallorn-trees and silver-lit fountains.","recentEvents":"Frodo and the Company are welcomed by Haldir and led to the city's high places, where they meet Celeborn and Galadriel. The group recounts Gandalf's fall in Moria, prompting sorrow and reflection.","relationships":[{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"Part of"}],"parentLocation":"Lothlórien"},{"name":"The Garden of Galadriel","aliases":["Silver Basin Garden"],"description":"A secluded garden at the southern slopes of Caras Galadhon, featuring a silver basin, ewer, and a fountain connected to the city's water supply.","recentEvents":"Galadriel leads Frodo and Sam to this garden, where she reveals the Mirror of Galadriel and tests their resolve with visions of their choices.","relationships":[{"location":"Caras Galadhon","relationship":"Adjacent"}]},{"name":"Hythe of Silverlode","aliases":["Silverlode Hythe"],"description":"A white-stone landing place by the Silverlode River where the Company prepares to depart Lothlórien.","recentEvents":"The Company received their boats and gifts here, with Elves providing waybread and elven-cloaks.","relationships":[{"location":"Silverlode River","relationship":"Part of"},{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"Bordering region"}],"parentLocation":"Silverlode River"},{"name":"Cataracts of Rauros","aliases":["Rauros Falls"],"description":"A perilous waterfall where the Great River (Anduin) plunges from Nen Hithoel, marking a dangerous obstacle.","recentEvents":"Celeborn warned the Company of the rapids and falls they would encounter downstream.","relationships":[{"location":"Great River","relationship":"Feature along"},{"location":"Tol Brandir","relationship":"Downstream from"}]},{"name":"End of Egladil","aliases":["Last End of Egladil"],"description":"A grassy plain at the southern edge of Lothlórien where the parting feast was held.","recentEvents":"The Company gathered for their farewell feast, with Galadriel presenting Aragorn with gifts.","relationships":[{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"Bordering region"}]},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall island where the Great River (Anduin) bends sharply, forming a landmark before the cataracts of Rauros.","recentEvents":"Celeborn described the River's course through Tol Brandir and its connection to the Dead Marshes.","relationships":[{"location":"Great River","relationship":"Geographical feature"}]},{"name":"Nindalf","aliases":["Wetwang"],"description":"A vast, sluggish fen where the Great River becomes divided and tortuous, bordered by the Entwash and Emyn Muil.","recentEvents":"Celeborn outlined the perilous terrain the Company would face after passing Rauros.","relationships":[{"location":"Great River","relationship":"Region along"},{"location":"Emyn Muil","relationship":"Adjacent to"}]},{"name":"Eastern Bank of the Great River Anduin","aliases":["Eastern Shore of Anduin"],"description":"A treeless, flat expanse with grass plains and distant hills, marked by the southernmost ranks of the Misty Mountains.","recentEvents":"The Company encountered orcs attacking their boats and faced the Sarn Gebir rapids, with Gollum's shadowy presence lingering.","relationships":[{"location":"Great River Anduin","relationship":"One of the river's banks"}]},{"name":"Limlight River","aliases":["North Boundary of Rohan"],"description":"A river marking the northern edge of Rohan, flowing into the Great River Anduin.","recentEvents":"The Company approached its confluence with Anduin, noting its historical ties to Rohan's past glory.","relationships":[{"location":"Rohan","relationship":"Northern boundary"},{"location":"Great River Anduin","relationship":"Confluence point"}]},{"name":"Sarn Gebir","aliases":["Rapids of Sarn Gebir"],"description":"Dangerous rapids on the Great River Anduin, where the Company narrowly avoided being swept downstream by orcs.","recentEvents":"A night attack by orcs and a perilous struggle to navigate the rapids tested the Company's resolve.","relationships":[{"location":"Great River Anduin","relationship":"Notable section of the river"}]},{"name":"Brown Lands","aliases":["Desolate Lands of Anduin"],"description":"A vast, barren region between Southern Mirkwood and the Emyn Muil, scorched by ancient evil.","recentEvents":"The Company traversed this desolate area, sensing lingering threats from the Enemy.","relationships":[{"location":"Emyn Muil","relationship":"Southern boundary"},{"location":"Southern Mirkwood","relationship":"Northern boundary"}]},{"name":"Western Bank of the Great River Anduin","aliases":["West bank of the Great River Anduin"],"arc":"Aragorn's Leadership and the Quest's Legacy","description":"A grassy plain along the western shore of the Great River Anduin, shaded by the hill of Amon Hen.","recentEvents":"Frodo and his companions rest here, but Frodo is tormented by visions of Mordor. Boromir's temptation by the Ring leads to a confrontation, culminating in Frodo's decision to depart alone.","relationships":[{"location":"Amon Hen","relationship":"Lies to the east of this bank"},{"location":"Eastern Bank of the Great River Anduin","relationship":"Opposite shore of the same river"}]},{"name":"Emyn Muil","aliases":["East Wall of Rohan"],"arc":"Frodo's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"A range of grey hills forming a natural barrier between the Shire and the Land of Shadow.","recentEvents":"Aragorn, Legolas, and Gimli traversed its ridges, tracking Orcs who had passed through the region.","relationships":[{"location":"Amon Lhaw","relationship":"Southern slopes of Amon Lhaw connect to the Emyn Muil"},{"location":"Rohan","relationship":"Forms the eastern border"},{"location":"White Mountains","relationship":"Separated by the plains of Rohan"}]},{"name":"Land of Shadow","description":"A dark, desolate region encompassing Mordor and its surrounding areas, associated with evil and darkness.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam head towards the Land of Shadow as they depart from the Emyn Muil.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Part of the broader Land of Shadow"}]},{"name":"Entwash Vale","aliases":["Entwade","Entwash"],"description":"A major river flowing through the northern reaches of the Wold, marking the boundary between Rohan and Fangorn.","recentEvents":"Aragorn finds hobbit footprints near the riverbank, indicating the hobbits' recent presence.","relationships":[{"location":"Entwash","relationship":"Defined by the river's course"},{"location":"Fangorn","relationship":"Lies to the north of this region"},{"location":"Rohan","relationship":"Bordering region of Rohan"},{"location":"Entwash Vale","relationship":"Adjacent to the Entwash River"},{"location":"Wold","relationship":"Marks the southern edge of the region"},{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Serves as the route to the Rohirrim capital"},{"location":"Entwade","relationship":"Converges with the Entwade near the river's mouth"},{"location":"Fangorn Forest","relationship":"Bordering the forest"},{"location":"Entwash River","relationship":"Primary waterway through the valley"}]},{"name":"Ring of the Orcs","description":"A large, trampled clearing where Orcs rested during their march.","recentEvents":"Aragorn identified this site as where the Orcs had paused, with tracks indicating they had left hours earlier.","relationships":[{"location":"Emyn Muil","relationship":"Located within the highland range"},{"location":"Downs","relationship":"Adjacent to the southern slopes"}]},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","aliases":["Fangorn"],"arc":"Frodo's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"An ancient forest in the north of Middle-earth, home to the Ents and the last remnants of the Old Forest.","recentEvents":"Aragorn, Legolas, and Gimli track hobbits through the forest, discovering footprints and encountering Gandalf in disguise as Saruman.","relationships":[{"location":"Entwash","relationship":"Borders the western edge of the forest"},{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Lies beyond the forest's eastern reaches"},{"location":"Entwash Vale","relationship":"Adjacent to the forest"},{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"Distant region; Gandalf references its connection to the mallorn leaf"}]},{"name":"Wold","description":"A rolling grassland region between the Entwash and the southern reaches of Rohan, often shrouded in mist.","recentEvents":"The group traverses this area, encountering the aftermath of a battle and the eerie presence of the forest.","relationships":[{"location":"Entwash","relationship":"Flows through the northern part of the region"},{"location":"Fangorn","relationship":"Lies to the east, bordering the forest"}]},{"name":"Wellinghall","aliases":["Ent-house"],"description":"A vast subterranean hall formed by the roots of ancient trees, with a central stone table and glowing water vessels.","recentEvents":"The hobbits stay here overnight, drinking enchanted water and discussing their journey with Treebeard.","relationships":[{"location":"Fangorn Forest","relationship":"Part of"}],"parentLocation":"Fangorn"},{"name":"Derndingle","aliases":["The Dingle"],"description":"A vast bowl-shaped glade surrounded by towering evergreen trees, with a central spring and three silver-birches.","recentEvents":"The Ents gathered for the Entmoot, a rare assembly to discuss threats to their lands. Treebeard and Bregalad welcomed the hobbits, who observed the Ents' deliberations and the growing resolve to confront Isengard.","relationships":[{"location":"Fangorn Forest","relationship":"Part of"},{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"Target of impending action"}],"parentLocation":"Fangorn"},{"name":"Deeping-coomb","aliases":["Deeping Coomb"],"description":"A valley where the enemy is trapped after the battle","recentEvents":"The hosts of Isengard are now trapped in the Deeping-coomb, fleeing under the trees","relationships":[{"location":"Helm’s Deep","relationship":"Adjacent valley where the enemy is cornered"}]},{"name":"Road to Isengard","aliases":["Isengard Road","Southward Road","South Road"],"arc":"Rohan's Defense and Strategic Movements","description":"The path leading from the Hornburg to Isengard, marked by its journey through Fangorn Forest and the Fords of Isen.","recentEvents":"Wains carrying refugees and soldiers travel along this route, with three distinct lines of traffic.","relationships":[{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"leads to"},{"location":"Fords of Isen","relationship":"connects to"},{"location":"Morannon","relationship":"Extends southward from the Black Gate"},{"location":"Ithilien","relationship":"Passes through the region's northern marches"},{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Primary southern exit"},{"location":"Osgiliath","relationship":"Connects to the Road to Isengard"}]},{"name":"Fords of Isen","aliases":["Isen Fords"],"description":"A critical crossing point on the Road to Isengard, where the riverbed is dry and silent due to Saruman's influence.","recentEvents":"The company approaches the Fords, noting the river's desolation and the wolves' absence, as Gandalf ensures their safe passage.","relationships":[{"location":"Road to Isengard","relationship":"part of"},{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"leads to"}],"parentLocation":"Road to Isengard"},{"name":"Deeping-stream","aliases":["Deeping Stream"],"description":"A stream near the Hornburg where Théoden and Gandalf reunite after the battle, symbolizing the transition from war to diplomacy.","recentEvents":"Théoden and Gandalf meet here, planning the journey to Isengard and reflecting on the battle's aftermath.","relationships":[{"location":"Hornburg","relationship":"near"},{"location":"Road to Isengard","relationship":"connects to"}]},{"name":"Death Down","description":"A desolate area where Orcs were slain and buried by the Ents.","recentEvents":"The Ents destroyed the Orcs here, leaving a barren, grassless wasteland.","relationships":[{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"Located in the valley beneath Isengard"}]},{"name":"Wizard's Vale (Nan Curunír)","aliases":["Nan Curunír"],"description":"A sheltered valley once fertile but now transformed into a wasteland by Saruman's industrialization.","recentEvents":"The group passed through this valley, witnessing its deforestation and pollution caused by Isengard's operations.","relationships":[{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"The valley beneath Isengard's ring-wall"}]},{"name":"Orthanc","aliases":["Tower of Orthanc"],"arc":"Dwarven Alliances and the Lonely Mountain (dormant)","description":"A towering stone fortress carved into the heart of Isengard, with a dark, imposing structure and a single entrance via a flight of stairs.","recentEvents":"Gandalf and Théoden confront Saruman, who attempts to manipulate them with his persuasive voice. Saruman's staff is broken by Gandalf, and he is cast down from the tower after being denounced as a liar and corrupter.","relationships":[{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"Central structure of the region"},{"location":"Fangorn Forest","relationship":"Adjacent to the ravine leading to Orthanc"}]},{"name":"Ruins of the Gate","aliases":["Gate of Isengard"],"arc":"Rohan's Defense, Ents' Rebellion, and the Fall of Isengard","description":"The collapsed entrance to Isengard where Gandalf and the Company exit Orthanc.","recentEvents":"Gandalf and the Company leave Orthanc, encountering Treebeard and the Ents at the gate ruins.","relationships":[{"location":"Orthanc","relationship":"Exit point"},{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"Boundary"}]},{"name":"Watchwood","aliases":["Ents' Watch"],"description":"A forested area the Ents will transform into a surveillance zone to monitor Saruman.","recentEvents":"Treebeard vows to flood the valley and create the Watchwood to trap Saruman.","relationships":[{"location":"Fangorn Forest","relationship":"Adjacent territory"},{"location":"Orthanc","relationship":"Monitoring target"}]},{"name":"Dale of Dol Baran","aliases":["Dol Baran Dale"],"description":"A secluded valley nestled beneath the northern mountain ranges, where the group camps after leaving Isengard.","recentEvents":"Gandalf and the company rest here, with Pippin secretly examining the Palantír and encountering visions of Saruman.","relationships":[{"location":"Dol Baran","relationship":"Slopes of the hill form the northern boundary of the dale"},{"location":"Road to Isengard","relationship":"The dale lies along the route toward Helm’s Deep"}]},{"name":"Thrihyrne Peaks","aliases":["White Mountains"],"description":"A range of jagged peaks forming part of the White Mountains, visible under the stars during the journey.","recentEvents":"Gandalf and Pippin pass near these peaks while riding toward Minas Tirith, with the stars illuminating their path.","relationships":[{"location":"White Mountains","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Westfold Dales","description":"A valley leading eastward toward the road to Edoras, marked by the approach of the Deeping-coomb.","recentEvents":"The path through the Westfold dales is taken as Gandalf and Pippin head toward Edoras and Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Approaching"}]},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","aliases":["The Morgul Pass","Stairs of Cirith Ungol","Shelob’s Lair (Torech Ungol)"],"arc":"Sam's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"A treacherous mountain pass known for its deadly traps and the Silent Watchers, a hidden evil force within its walls.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam enter Shelob’s Lair, a vast subterranean webbed chamber, and escape after a deadly confrontation with the giant spider Shelob.","relationships":[{"location":"Ephel Dúath","relationship":"Located within the shadowy mountain range"},{"location":"Morannon","relationship":"A separate but similarly perilous route within Mordor's borders"},{"location":"Minas Morgul","relationship":"Linked via the Morgul Valley and the Road to Isengard"},{"location":"Morgul Vale","relationship":"Surrounds the pass on all sides"},{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Part of the region's northern boundary"}]},{"name":"Morannon","aliases":["Black Gate"],"description":"The fortress of Mordor, where the Black Gate stands as a formidable barrier.","recentEvents":"A horn was blown on its ramparts as Men from the South approached Mordor.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Part of"}],"parentLocation":"Mordor"},{"name":"South beyond the Great River’s end","aliases":["Southern reaches of the Great River"],"description":"A region beyond the Great River Anduin where new threats emerge.","recentEvents":"Men from the South, clad in red and gold, marched toward the Black Gate.","relationships":[{"location":"Great River Anduin","relationship":"Beyond"}]},{"name":"Ithilien","arc":"Aragorn's Leadership and the War Against Sauron (Indirect)","description":"A region south of Minas Tirith, known for its river valleys and the presence of the Ring-bearer's journey.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam are blindfolded by Faramir to a hidden location within Ithilien, where they witness the sunset from the Window of the Sunset (Henneth Annûn).","relationships":[{"location":"Ephel Dúath","relationship":"Bound by mountain ranges to the east"},{"location":"Road to Isengard","relationship":"Traveled southward along this ancient route"},{"location":"Henneth Annûn","relationship":"Contains the Window of the Sunset"}]},{"name":"Cloven Way","aliases":["Road through the Cloven Way"],"description":"A narrow, treacherous path through Ithilien's rugged terrain, used for secret movements.","recentEvents":"Faramir's Rangers ambush Men of Harad marching along this route, leading to a fierce battle.","relationships":[{"location":"Ithilien","relationship":"Part of"}],"parentLocation":"Ithilien"},{"name":"Road above Rauros","aliases":["High Road over Rauros"],"description":"A elevated path crossing the Cataracts of Rauros, strategically important for military movements.","recentEvents":"Gondor's forces use this road to intercept Haradrim troops, resulting in a chaotic clash with a Mûmak.","relationships":[{"location":"Cataracts of Rauros","relationship":"Adjacent to"}]},{"name":"Henneth Annûn","aliases":["Window of the Sunset"],"arc":"Frodo's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"A natural rock formation in Ithilien where the sunlight refracts through water, creating a dazzling display.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Faramir observe the Forbidden Pool from its cliffs; Gollum is captured after being discovered fishing there.","relationships":[{"location":"Ithilien","relationship":"Located within Ithilien"},{"location":"Forbidden Pool","relationship":"Adjacent to the southern bank of the cave"}]},{"name":"Forbidden Pool","aliases":["Forbidden Pool"],"description":"A dark, dangerous waterway within Henneth Annûn, known for its treacherous currents and hidden dangers.","recentEvents":"Gollum is lured to the pool by the promise of fish, leading to his capture by Faramir's men.","relationships":[{"location":"Henneth Annûn","relationship":"Located within the cave complex"}]},{"name":"Morgul Valley","aliases":["Valley of the Wraiths","Morgul Vale"],"arc":"Frodo's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"A desolate region plagued by the influence of the Nazgûl, marked by the polluted Morgulduin stream.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam crossed the bridge over the valley, witnessing the departure of Morgul's army and the city's eerie glow.","relationships":[{"location":"Ithilien","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Bordering territory"},{"location":"Minas Morgul","relationship":"Contains the city"},{"location":"Cirith Ungol","relationship":"Encircled by the valley"}]},{"name":"Cross-roads","aliases":["Four-way junction"],"arc":"Frodo's Burden and the Ring's Power","description":"A critical intersection where four roads converge, central to the journey's climax.","recentEvents":"Frodo, Sam, and Gollum approach this strategic point under ominous circumstances.","relationships":[{"location":"Morgul Valley","relationship":"Southward access"},{"location":"Mountains of Gondor","relationship":"Northern boundary"}]},{"name":"Minas Morgul","aliases":["City of the Ringwraiths"],"arc":"Sauron's Watchful Eye","description":"A dark fortress perched on the Ephel Dúath, illuminated by a sickly light and guarded by an army of orcs and riders.","recentEvents":"A massive army marched from its gates, crossing the bridge toward Osgiliath as Frodo and Sam observed from the pass.","relationships":[{"location":"Cirith Ungol","relationship":"Visible from the pass"},{"location":"Morgul Vale","relationship":"Situated within the valley"}]},{"name":"Nameless Land","aliases":["Cirith Ungol Region"],"description":"A desolate region near the southern borders of Mordor, marked by its barren terrain and proximity to Shelob's lair.","recentEvents":"Sam battles Shelob, saves Frodo, and confronts Orcs after Frodo's apparent death. The Nameless Land becomes the site of Sam's pivotal decision to continue the quest.","relationships":[{"location":"Cirith Ungol","relationship":"Part of the same region"},{"location":"Morgul Vale","relationship":"Adjacent to the southern edge"}]},{"name":"Pelennor Fields","aliases":["Fields of the Pelennor","Pelennor"],"description":"The fertile plains surrounding Minas Tirith, enclosed by the out-wall built to defend against attacks.","recentEvents":"Pippin observes the movement of wains and troops preparing for war, with the Great Gate as the main entry point.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Surrounded by the Pelennor Fields"},{"location":"Anduin","relationship":"Bordering the western edge of the fields"}]},{"name":"Harlond","aliases":["Harlond Quays"],"description":"The waterfront district of Minas Tirith, where ships arrive from southern fiefs.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as part of the city's infrastructure during Gandalf's description of Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Part of the city's southern boundary"}]},{"name":"Mount Mindolluin","description":"The western spur of the White Mountains, forming the natural foundation of Minas Tirith.","recentEvents":"Described as the base upon which the city's walls are built, with the White Tower overlooking the Pelennor Fields.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Geographical foundation"}]},{"name":"Court of the Fountain","aliases":["Fountain Court"],"description":"A central courtyard within Minas Tirith's citadel, serving as a transitional space between the hall and outer structures.","recentEvents":"Pippin and Gandalf traverse this area after their audience with Denethor, leading to the stable visit.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Interior courtyard"}]},{"name":"Sixth Circle","aliases":["Stables of the Citadel"],"description":"A fortified area outside Minas Tirith's walls housing swift horses and errand-riders.","recentEvents":"Shadowfax is housed here, with Pippin and Beregond checking on the horse's condition.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Adjacent district"}]},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A region in Gondor's south, home to the fortress of Lebennin.","recentEvents":"Forlong the Fat, lord of Lossarnach, arrives with a small force to aid Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"location":"Lebennin","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Umbar","relationship":"Linked by the Black Fleet alliance"}]},{"name":"Ringló Vale","aliases":["Ringlo Vale"],"description":"A valley in the north of Gondor, known for its rugged terrain and strategic importance.","recentEvents":"Men from Ringló Vale marched to Minas Tirith to defend the city, led by Dervorin.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]},{"name":"Morthond","description":"A region in the north of Gondor, home to the Duinhir clan.","recentEvents":"The Duinhir and their sons joined the defense of Minas Tirith with bowmen.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]},{"name":"Blackroot Vale","description":"A fertile valley in Gondor, known for its agricultural lands.","recentEvents":"Men from Blackroot Vale arrived at Minas Tirith, contributing to the city's defense.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]},{"name":"Anfalas","description":"A region in Gondor's west, bordering the Sea of Rhûn.","recentEvents":"A diverse group of men from Anfalas, including hunters and herdsmen, joined the defense of Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]},{"name":"Langstrand","description":"A coastal region in Gondor, known for its distant location and varied inhabitants.","recentEvents":"Men from Langstrand, including fisher-folk, arrived at Minas Tirith to defend the city.","relationships":[{"location":"Min,as Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]},{"name":"Lamedon","description":"A region in Gondor's north, characterized by its hillmen and isolated settlements.","recentEvents":"Grim hillmen from Lamedon arrived at Minas Tirith, though without a captain.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]},{"name":"Ethir","description":"A region in Gondor's west, known for its coastal settlements and maritime activities.","recentEvents":"A hundred fisher-folk from Ethir were spared from the Black fleet and joined the defense of Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]},{"name":"Pinnath Gelin","description":"A hill region in Gondor, known for its green-clad warriors.","recentEvents":"Hirluin the Fair and three hundred green-clad men from Pinnath Gelin arrived at Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]},{"name":"Dol Amroth","description":"A coastal city-state in Gondor, renowned for its naval power and the House of Imrahil.","recentEvents":"Imrahil, Prince of Dol Amroth, led seven hundred men at arms to Minas Tirith, accompanied by gilded banners.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Supplying defenders"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Sam's Burden and the Ring's Power","status":"active","characters":["Samwise Gamgee","Frodo Baggins","Gollum","Shelob"],"summary":"Sam saves Frodo from Shelob but finds him seemingly lifeless. After a moment of despair, Sam takes the Ring and resolves to continue the quest, pursuing the Orcs who have taken Frodo's body."},{"name":"Aragorn's Leadership and the War Against Sauron (Indirect)","status":"active","characters":["Aragorn","Faramir","Denethor"],"summary":"Faramir's perilous errand and the strategic preparations for the southern fleet's attack underscore Aragorn's indirect role in coordinating Gondor's defense. Denethor's prophetic visions and the looming threat of a 'great war' are emphasized."},{"name":"Dwarven Alliances and the Lonely Mountain (dormant)","status":"dormant","characters":["Gimli son of Glóin","Thorin Oakenshield","Balin"],"summary":"While Glóin's presence at the Council highlights the Dwarves' precarious situation, the chapter's focus shifts to the Ring's history and Gollum's escape. The Dwarven alliance's immediate relevance is paused, though its long-term implications remain tied to the broader conflict."},{"name":"Black Riders' Threat","status":"active","characters":["Pippin Took","Beregond","Bergil"],"summary":"The Black Riders' menace is confirmed as a direct threat to Gondor, with their connection to the southern fleet from Umbar now explicitly tied to Sauron's broader strategy. Pippin's awareness of their presence heightens the tension."},{"name":"Rohan's Defense and Strategic Movements","status":"active","characters":["Éomer","Beregond","Pippin"],"summary":"Rohan's strategic importance is highlighted as the southern fleet's arrival threatens to divert resources from the eastern front. Beregond's remarks about Rohan's potential role in the coming conflict are reinforced."},{"name":"Sauron's Watchful Eye","status":"active","characters":["Sauron","Black Riders","Shelob"],"summary":"The Black Riders are explicitly linked to Sauron's surveillance network, with their role in the southern fleet's attack confirming Shelob's lair as part of a larger, coordinated strategy to crush Gondor."}],"summary":"The chapter details the arrival of various regional militias to Minas Tirith, including men from Ringló Vale, Morthond, and Dol Amroth, to defend the city against looming threats. Pippin reflects on the grim reality of the war, while Gandalf warns of the approaching darkness, setting the stage for the city's critical defense."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":54,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3: THE RING GOES SOUTH","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The first Hobbit to become famous in the world at large, known for his journey into the East and return, which later involved all Hobbits in great events.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Heir and close companion"},{"character":"Gandalf the Grey","relationship":"Friend and advisor"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Friend and advisor"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of mithril rings and the legacy of Moria"},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Frodo"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter 10: THE CHOICES OF MASTER SAMWISE","currentLocation":"Near Cirith Ungol","description":"Carried across the river by the elf-horse, Frodo confronts the Black Riders and is swept away by the river's flood.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Heir and ancestor"},{"character":"Gandalf the Grey","relationship":"Mentor and companion"},{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Accompanied by Sam, who remains loyal despite doubts"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Gildor Inglorion","relationship":"Engaged in conversation about the world's dangers and Frodo's quest"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Guest at his house"},{"character":"Goldberry","relationship":"Guest at his house"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Companion and protector"},{"character":"Glorfindel","relationship":"Rescuer"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Companion and fellow traveler"},{"character":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","relationship":"Companion and potential leader"},{"character":"Gimli son of Glóin","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Recipient of the light-filled phial"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Companion and leader of the Company"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Accompanied by Gollum, who claims to know a secret path"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Subject to interrogation about Boromir’s death"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Companion and loyal friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by Orcs, poisoned by Shelob"},{"name":"Bandobras Took","aliases":["Bullroarer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"PROLOGUE","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A notable Hobbit from ancient times, known for being four foot five and able to ride a horse, surpassing many in Hobbit records.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in the context of Hobbit history and the development of their elusiveness."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Master of Buckland"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"PROLOGUE","currentLocation":"High Hay","description":"A Hobbit who compiled information about pipe-weed and its origins, contributing to Hobbit lore.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Documented the history of pipe-weed cultivation and its spread among Hobbits and other races."},{"name":"Dúnedain","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"PROLOGUE","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The people of the North Kingdom, remnants of the kings of Men who came over the Sea from Westernesse.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Hobbits in the westlands of Eriador, influencing Hobbit settlement and culture."},{"name":"Elves","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 8: FAREWELL TO LÓRIEN","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"Ancient beings who preserved records of the Elder Days and taught languages and crafts to Men and Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Imprisoned"}],"recentEvents":"Gave gifts of food, clothing, and ropes to the Company"},{"name":"The Butterbur Family","aliases":["Barliman Butterbur","Mr. Butterbur"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 11: A KNIFE IN THE DARK","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The family that has kept the inn The Prancing Pony in Bree since ancient times.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Suspicious of"}],"recentEvents":"Lost ponies, arranged for a replacement, and faced accusations of negligence."},{"name":"Gandalf the White","aliases":["Gandalf","Gandalf the Grey"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: MINAS TIRITH","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A wizard who reappeared after a three-year absence, now warning Frodo about the dangers of the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and advisor"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Leader of the Fellowship"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Respected companion"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Former colleague and adversary"},{"character":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","relationship":"Mentor and companion"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Gimli son of Glóin","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Théoden son of Thengel","relationship":"Advisor and mentor"},{"character":"Háma","relationship":"Debated entry protocols"},{"character":"Wormtongue","relationship":"Opponent and former manipulator"},{"character":"Éomer son of Éomund","relationship":"Allies in the war effort"},{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Collaborated to defeat Saruman"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Allied ruler of Rohan"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Mentor and guardian"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Advisor to the Steward of Gondor"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Minas Tirith, conversed with Pippin"},{"name":"Gollum [Sméagol]","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 9: SHELOB’S LAIR","currentLocation":"Near Cirith Ungol","description":"A former hobbit corrupted by the Ring, leading the group through the dangerous marshes.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Enemy"},{"character":"Déagol","relationship":"Murdered friend"},{"character":"Elves","relationship":"Imprisoned"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Carries the Ring; Gollum seeks to destroy it"},{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Deceitful ally with hidden motives"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Warned about his dangerous nature"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Observed and followed"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to ambush Frodo and Sam, but was defeated by Sam"},{"name":"Thorin Oakenshield","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Of the Finding of the Ring","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Leader of the dwarves on a quest for treasure, slain in the Battle of Five Armies.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Died in the Battle of Five Armies, with his hoard destroyed."},{"name":"Ham Gamgee","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Old gardener and friend of Bilbo and Frodo, known for his tales of Bilbo's wealth.","relationships":[{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke about Bilbo's treasure, discussed the party, and interacted with guests."},{"name":"Sam Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 9: SHELOB’S LAIR","currentLocation":"Near Cirith Ungol","description":"Frodo's loyal gardener and companion. Noted the Black Rider's presence and provided crucial information about the stranger in Hobbiton.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Travel companion and loyal friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Companion and friend"},{"character":"Fro, Baggins","relationship":"Traveling companion"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Rescued by"},{"character":"Goldberry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Suspicious of"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Gandalf the Grey","relationship":"Mentor"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Companion and friend"},{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Visited by Galadriel in her realm"},{"character":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","relationship":"Leader of the Company"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Suspicious of Gollum's true intentions but forced to rely on him"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Captured by soldiers"}],"recentEvents":"Fought Shelob's web, aided Frodo in breaking her web, and fled the lair."},{"name":"Old Noakes","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Hobbit from Bywater who discussed rumors about Frodo's family.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Commented on Frodo's Brandybuck heritage and Bilbo's wealth."},{"name":"Daddy Twofoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Neighbor of the Gaffer, known for his opinions on local matters.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Neighbor"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke about the Brandybucks and their connection to the Old Forest."},{"name":"Stranger from Michel Delving","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Michel Delving","description":"Visitor from the Westfarthing who speculated about Bilbo's treasure.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Talked about Bilbo's rumored tunnels and wealth."},{"name":"Sackville-Bagginses","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Family of hobbits who scowled at Bilbo's announcement.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed in wrath after Bilbo's disappearance."},{"name":"Old Odo Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Hobbit with large, furry feet who commented on Bilbo's disappearance.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Suspected Bilbo's disappearance was not a prank."},{"name":"Adelard Took","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Recipient of an umbrella labeled 'For Adelard Took, for his VERY OWN, from Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an umbrella from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Dora Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Drogo’s sister and the eldest surviving female relative of Bilbo and Frodo; ninety-nine years old.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a waste-paper basket labeled 'For Dora Baggins in memory of a LONG correspondence'."},{"name":"Milo Burrows","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Recipient of a gold pen and ink-bottle labeled 'For Milo Burrows, hoping it will be useful, from B.B'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a gold pen and ink-bottle from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Angelica","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A young Baggins who received a round convex mirror labeled 'For Angelica’s use, from Uncle Bilbo'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received a mirror from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Hugo Bracegirdle","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A collector of books who received an empty book-case labeled 'For the collection of Hugo Bracegirdle'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an empty book-case from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s relative who took silver spoons labeled 'For Lobelia Sackville-Baggins, as a PRESENT'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over spoons and left with them."},{"name":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s heir (before Frodo’s adoption) who demanded to see Frodo’s will.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over the will and left in frustration."},{"name":"Sancho Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Old Odo Proudfoot’s grandson who excavated the pantry seeking Bilbo’s gold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Attempted to excavate the pantry and was ejected by Frodo."},{"name":"Merry Brandybuck","aliases":["Master of Buckland","Merry"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE PASSING OF THE GREY COMPANY","currentLocation":"Rohan","description":"A hobbit who joined the company of the Ring and was presumed lost but was found feasting in Isengard","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Close friend and companion"},{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Met and conversed with during their journey"},{"character":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Gimli son of Glóin","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Legolas Greenleaf","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Cousin"},{"character":"Gandalf the White","relationship":"Mentor and companion"},{"character":"Théoden son of Thengel","relationship":"Esquire"}],"recentEvents":"Was appointed Théoden's esquire, received a sword from the king, and accompanied the Riders of Rohan to the Hornburg."},{"name":"Ted Sandyman","aliases":["Sandyman"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE SHADOW OF THE PAST","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A miller's son who engaged in conversation with Sam Gamgee about rumors of strange events in the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Ham Gamgee","relationship":"Neighbor"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in a discussion at The Green Dragon about rumors of elves, giants, and dragons."},{"name":"Déagol","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE SHADOW OF THE PAST","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A hobbit who discovered the One Ring but was murdered by Sméagol.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by Sméagol after being robbed of the Ring."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Strider","Aragorn","Aragorn [Strider]"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: THE PASSING OF THE GREY COMPANY","currentLocation":"Storm of Mordor","description":"Leader of the Company, bearing the sword Andúril, guides the group through the dale and towards Lothlórien.","rela