 estate."},{"name":"Hugo Bracegirdle","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A collector of books who received an empty book-case labeled 'For the collection of Hugo Bracegirdle'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received an empty book-case from Bilbo's estate."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s relative who took silver spoons labeled 'For Lobelia Sackville-Baggins, as a PRESENT'.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over spoons and left with them."},{"name":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Bilbo’s heir (before Frodo’s adoption) who demanded to see Frodo’s will.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Argued with Frodo over the will and left in frustration."},{"name":"Sancho Proudfoot","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Old Odo Proudfoot’s grandson who excavated the pantry seeking Bilbo’s gold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Attempted to excavate the pantry and was ejected by Frodo."},{"name":"Merry Brandybuck","aliases":["Master of Buckland","Merry"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 5: THE RIDE OF THE ROHIRRIM","currentLocation":"With Théoden's forces","description":"A hobbit who joined the company of the Ring and was presumed lost but was found feasting in Isengard","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Close friend and companion"},{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Met and conversed with during their journey"},{"character":"Arago